ack]]\n| 185 || \u2014\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes that the recording did not chart.\n|}\n\n=== Compilation albums ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of live albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Release\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.6em; font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"Billboard\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Two Trips''\n|\n* Released: 1970\n* Label: Mercury\n* Formats: LP\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''The Best of the Youngbloods''\n|\n* Released: 1970\n* Label: RCA Victor\n* Formats: LP, CD, cassette\n| 144\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Sunlight''\n|\n* Released: 1970\n* Label: RCA Victor\n* Formats: LP\n| 186\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes that the recording did not chart.\n|}\n\n=== Live albums ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of live albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Release\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.6em; font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"Billboard\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.6em; font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br /><ref name=\"CAN-1\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|  ''[[Rock Festival (album)|Rock Festival]]''\n|\n* Released: 1970\n* Label: Racoon Records\n* Formats: LP, CD, cassette\n| 89 || 73\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|  ''Ride the Wind''\n|\n* Released: 1971\n* Label: Racoon Records\n* Formats: LP, CD, 8-track\n| 157 || \u2014\n|-\n| colspan=\"10\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes that the recording did not chart.\n|}\n\n=== Reissue albums ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable pla